1400
01:17:43,667 --> 01:17:46,733
Dudley and Mom.
It was fun!

1401
01:17:50,002 --> 01:17:51,977
Dudley went skating
with you?

1402
01:17:52,051 --> 01:17:55,346
We waited for you, Henry.
You didn't miss much at all.

1403
01:18:00,210 --> 01:18:02,414
[Dog Barking]

1404
01:18:02,482 --> 01:18:06,955
Ah, Henry! Just the man I wanted
to see. I've been working on this...

1405
01:18:07,026 --> 01:18:09,874
Keep away from my wife.

1406
01:18:09,939 --> 01:18:11,979
What'd I do now?

1407
01:18:12,051 --> 01:18:14,866
- You take her to lunch.
- Well, you were late, Henry.

1408
01:18:14,931 --> 01:18:17,135
- You take her to Jazzies.
- You asked me to.

1409
01:18:17,203 --> 01:18:20,552
You take her skating.
What kind of man do you think I am?

1410
01:18:20,626 --> 01:18:23,277
Keep the hell away from her.

1411
01:18:23,346 --> 01:18:25,735
Henry, you're a man of God.

1412
01:18:25,811 --> 01:18:29,772
That doesn't mean I'm blind.
Now, I've seen the way she looks at you.

1413
01:18:29,843 --> 01:18:33,105
Really? I mean, really.

1414
01:18:33,171 --> 01:18:36,880
All right, fine.
I want you to leave now.

1415
01:18:36,946 --> 01:18:39,019
- Now?
- Yes, now. [Opens Door]

1416
01:18:39,091 --> 01:18:42,407
I don't think I can do that.
Check the angel handbook.

1417
01:18:42,483 --> 01:18:45,101
It says I can't leave
until I'm through, I think.

1418
01:18:45,170 --> 01:18:47,210
[Muttering]
You see, it says right here...

1419
01:18:47,283 --> 01:18:49,650
Wait a minute.
Hey! Henry!

1420
01:18:51,442 --> 01:18:53,679
What was that?

1421
01:18:53,747 --> 01:18:58,482
- Oooh!
- My goodness!

1422
01:18:58,547 --> 01:19:01,362
- What?
- You're in trouble.

1423
01:19:01,427 --> 01:19:03,631
What was that?
What is that?

1424
01:19:03,699 --> 01:19:05,903
It wasn't a sign
that there's a new pope.

1425
01:19:05,971 --> 01:19:08,971
- What do you mean?
- You're in trouble.
You want me out of the house.

1426
01:19:09,043 --> 01:19:12,076
- Yes, I want you out.
- I'm not the problem. It wasn't me.

1427
01:19:12,179 --> 01:19:14,732
- It wasn't me!
- Who are you talking to?
Get out of my house!

1428
01:19:14,803 --> 01:19:16,974
What is going on in here?

1429
01:19:17,043 --> 01:19:20,272
- I am terminating Dudley's services.
- Is that what you want, Julia?

1430
01:19:20,338 --> 01:19:23,633
It isn't a question of what she wants.

1431
01:19:23,699 --> 01:19:27,081
All right, Julia, you're a part of this.
You say.

1432
01:19:27,187 --> 01:19:31,213
You two stop this right now.
Just stop it!

1433
01:19:31,283 --> 01:19:34,065
You hear me?
[Slams Door]

1434
01:19:36,083 --> 01:19:38,319
- [Henry] You see what you did?
- It's not about me.

1435
01:19:38,386 --> 01:19:41,452
You and Julia would have these problems
even if I never showed up.

1436
01:19:41,522 --> 01:19:45,451
You've forgotten what's important,
for you and for her.

1437
01:19:45,523 --> 01:19:48,010
And you're going to remind me, I'm sure.

1438
01:19:48,082 --> 01:19:50,864
St. Matt's is more
than just a church, Henry.

1439
01:19:50,931 --> 01:19:53,745
It's the glue that holds everything
together in this neighborhood.

1440
01:19:53,811 --> 01:19:57,705
And you mark my word, without it, this
neighborhood will fall, I guarantee it.

1441
01:19:57,778 --> 01:20:01,324
And Julia will never look at you
the same. [Door Opens]

1442
01:20:11,122 --> 01:20:14,090
Hey, handsome.
Come and walk me across the street.

1443
01:20:14,162 --> 01:20:16,781
I gotta take this plate
over to Bessie Adams.

1444
01:20:16,851 --> 01:20:19,665
- Well, actually, I was...
- Walk me!

1445
01:20:19,731 --> 01:20:21,519
Delighted.

1446
01:20:26,898 --> 01:20:29,833
- I heard what you two
were talking about.
- Really?

1447
01:20:29,907 --> 01:20:34,315
Now, you know I don't usually
pry into other folks' business.

1448
01:20:34,387 --> 01:20:37,005
- Uh-huh.
- Hold on a second.

1449
01:20:39,218 --> 01:20:41,520
Mmm-mm!

1450
01:20:42,739 --> 01:20:47,179
Now, what are you doing
to my daughter?

1451
01:20:47,250 --> 01:20:50,185
Mrs. Coleman, it's all right,
I promise you.

1452
01:20:50,259 --> 01:20:55,758
Nothin' is all right, Dudley, when I see
a married woman look at a man that way.

1453
01:20:55,827 --> 01:20:58,860
I'm just tryin' to help them,
that's all.

1454
01:20:58,930 --> 01:21:01,199
[Laughs, Coughing]

1455
01:21:01,267 --> 01:21:04,081
You really shouldn't smoke.
Our time here on Earth is precious.

1456
01:21:04,178 --> 01:21:06,088
That's right.

1457
01:21:06,163 --> 01:21:10,799
And you know the most precious time
of all is time spent with your family.

1458
01:21:10,867 --> 01:21:14,511
Now, you know I'm supposed
to only be here through Christmas.

1459
01:21:14,578 --> 01:21:17,840
But I will conveniently
have a hip injury...

1460
01:21:17,907 --> 01:21:20,143
and stay to the year 2000
if I have to.

1461
01:21:20,211 --> 01:21:22,349
Do you understand
what I'm sayin' to you?

1462
01:21:22,418 --> 01:21:24,273
- I do now.
- Mm-hmm.

1463
01:21:24,338 --> 01:21:27,950
Look, I'm havin' a little trouble
tryin' to get through to Henry.

1464
01:21:28,018 --> 01:21:31,018
Now, Julia, on the other hand,
she's wonderful. She deserves...

1465
01:21:31,091 --> 01:21:34,058
What are you talkin' about what Julia
deserves and what she don't?

1466
01:21:34,130 --> 01:21:36,813
She's Henry's wife.

1467
01:21:36,882 --> 01:21:38,890
Don't worry. L...

1468
01:21:38,963 --> 01:21:42,792
I'm sure she'll forget me
as soon as I leave.

1469
01:21:42,867 --> 01:21:46,031
She'll forget herself
if you go on like this.

1470
01:21:46,099 --> 01:21:48,303
[Bessie]
Marguerite, is that you?

1471
01:21:48,371 --> 01:21:50,345
I'm comin', Bessie!

1472
01:21:50,418 --> 01:21:54,248
Now, Dudley, you are a charming person.

1473
01:21:54,323 --> 01:21:56,973
You go charm somebody else.

1474
01:21:57,042 --> 01:21:59,279
Okay?

1475
01:22:10,482 --> 01:22:13,352
Bessie, I'm comin' in.

1476
01:22:13,427 --> 01:22:16,623
Did I tell you I quit smokin'?

1477
01:22:16,690 --> 01:22:18,992
[Bessie]
I'm so proud of you, sugar.

1478
01:22:19,058 --> 01:22:22,571
[Chattering Continues]

1479
01:22:24,402 --> 01:22:26,409
[Saul]
Watch it. Don't slip now.

1480
01:22:26,482 --> 01:22:30,410
Come on, babies, let's go. Thank you
so much. Now you have a lot more room.

1481
01:22:30,482 --> 01:22:32,970
- Bye.
- Hi, Dudley!

1482
01:22:33,042 --> 01:22:36,337
- I'm just baby-sitting Jeremiah.
- [Chuckles]

1483
01:22:36,402 --> 01:22:39,468
- Mommy, Mommy! Here, puppy.
- Get away from that dog!

1484
01:22:39,538 --> 01:22:41,840
- Go ahead!
- Jeremiah! Jeremiah!

1485
01:22:41,906 --> 01:22:43,761
[Beverly]
Saul!

1486
01:22:43,826 --> 01:22:46,892
[Man On Bus]
Where's he goin'now?

1487
01:22:46,962 --> 01:22:51,370
Thank you so much for the ride.
I know you had to go out of your way.

1488
01:22:51,442 --> 01:22:55,817
The first five minutes of The Nutcracker
hasn't changed any since last year.

1489
01:22:55,890 --> 01:22:59,370
- I'll make 'em leave before the bows
so we can come and get you.
- Oh, thank you.

1490
01:22:59,442 --> 01:23:01,679
- [Laughs] Um...
- Um...

1491
01:23:01,746 --> 01:23:04,615
- [Laughing] Thanks.
- [Laughing]

1492
01:23:04,690 --> 01:23:07,854
Okay.
[Laughing Continues]

1493
01:23:07,922 --> 01:23:10,257
- Bye-bye.
- Bye!

1494
01:23:10,323 --> 01:23:13,584
[Man On Bus] No time for that, Saul.
Come on, we're gonna be late.

1495
01:23:13,651 --> 01:23:17,447
Oh, Santa, just leave that man
under my tree... if he'll fit.

1496
01:23:18,803 --> 01:23:22,545
% We all want to make
a place in this world%

1497
01:23:22,738 --> 01:23:27,441
% We all want our voices
to be heard%

1498
01:23:27,507 --> 01:23:30,540
% Everyone%

1499
01:23:30,610 --> 01:23:34,571
% Wants a chance to be someone%

1500
01:23:34,642 --> 01:23:38,570
% We all have dreams
we need to dream%

1501
01:23:38,642 --> 01:23:43,377
% Sweeter than any star
you can reach%

1502
01:23:43,442 --> 01:23:47,087
% 'Cause when you reach and find%

1503
01:23:47,186 --> 01:23:50,896
% You've found someone%

1504
01:23:50,962 --> 01:23:54,824
% You'll hold this world's
most priceless thing%

1505
01:23:54,898 --> 01:23:58,891
% The greatest gift
this life can bring%

1506
01:23:58,962 --> 01:24:02,891
% Is when you look back and know%

1507
01:24:02,963 --> 01:24:06,311
% You were loved% %

1508
01:24:20,178 --> 01:24:23,855
Oh, Keeleys...
Take a left at Woodlawn.

1509
01:24:23,922 --> 01:24:26,191
The Keeleys live on Sixth.

1510
01:24:26,259 --> 01:24:29,936
Henry, the Keeleys
live on Woodlawn.

1511
01:24:31,602 --> 01:24:34,123
- You're jealous.
- I am not jealous.

1512
01:24:34,226 --> 01:24:37,522
- Yes, you are.
- I may be a lot of things,
but jealous is not one of them.

1513
01:24:37,587 --> 01:24:40,718
Sure, you are. You're so jealous,
you can't even think straight.

1514
01:24:40,786 --> 01:24:43,055
I am thinking just fine, thank you.

1515
01:24:43,122 --> 01:24:46,799
- You can't even remember
where the Keeleys live.
- The Keeleys' house is on Sixth.

1516
01:24:46,866 --> 01:24:49,419
- Then what's it doing over there?
- What?

1517
01:24:50,450 --> 01:24:53,582
Hmm.
[Opens Door]

1518
01:24:53,651 --> 01:24:56,717
[Muttering]
Keeleys moved.

1519
01:24:56,787 --> 01:24:59,689
Woodlawn. Sixth.

1520
01:24:59,763 --> 01:25:03,374
- Is this it?
- Mm-hmm. There's the house.

1521
01:25:03,442 --> 01:25:06,377
- Be careful, Henry.
- I will be.

1522
01:25:06,450 --> 01:25:09,745
Drive all this way,
they're probably not even home.

1523
01:25:11,730 --> 01:25:14,578
At least they could
shovel their walkway.

1524
01:25:16,306 --> 01:25:19,372
- Whoooaaah!
- [Gasps]

1525
01:25:23,122 --> 01:25:25,129
[Groaning]

1526
01:25:25,202 --> 01:25:29,032
Henry!
[Laughing]

1527
01:25:29,106 --> 01:25:32,074
What are you laughin' at?
[Laughing]

1528
01:25:32,178 --> 01:25:35,440
You look like a kid.
Are you all right?

1529
01:25:35,506 --> 01:25:37,611
- I'm fine.
- Let me help you up.

1530
01:25:37,682 --> 01:25:40,071
Thanks, babe.

1531
01:25:40,146 --> 01:25:43,594
- [Gasps]
- Oh, baby. What are you doing?

1532
01:25:43,667 --> 01:25:48,238
- I thought you was helpin'me up.
- You did this on purpose.
[Laughing Continues]

1533
01:25:48,306 --> 01:25:50,510
Eddie, come here quick.
It's the preacher.

1534
01:25:50,578 --> 01:25:53,927
- What's goin' on?
- I hope you didn't hurt yourself.

1535
01:25:54,002 --> 01:25:56,173
- You all right?
- We're fine.

1536
01:25:56,242 --> 01:25:58,577
I told these kids to shovel that walk.

1537
01:25:58,642 --> 01:26:01,293
They ain't got nothin' on their mind
but Santa Claus. Sorry.

1538
01:26:01,362 --> 01:26:03,533
- This is yours. Merry Christmas.
- Us?

1539
01:26:03,602 --> 01:26:06,090
- Merry Christmas.
- God bless you.

1540
01:26:06,162 --> 01:26:09,511
- You'll catch cold. Be careful.
- We will.

1541
01:26:09,586 --> 01:26:11,626
[Henry]
I'll see you on Sunday.

1542
01:26:11,698 --> 01:26:14,153
[Mr. Keeley]
We'll be there. All of us.

1543
01:26:15,922 --> 01:26:18,889
[Henry Sighs] Seems like
we've been doin' this forever.

1544
01:26:18,962 --> 01:26:22,191
Forever is right.
Do you remember the first time?

1545
01:26:22,258 --> 01:26:25,073
- My mother was visiting, yeah.
- Yes.

1546
01:26:25,138 --> 01:26:28,651
- You know, Henry, she never liked me.
- No, no, that's not true.

1547
01:26:28,722 --> 01:26:33,229
She used to say, "Girl, you better
get some meat on them there bones."

1548
01:26:33,298 --> 01:26:35,599
Well, she just wanted
you to eat, that's all.

1549
01:26:35,667 --> 01:26:38,798
- No, she wanted me to be as fat as her.
- She wasn't that fat.

1550
01:26:38,866 --> 01:26:43,438
Henry, a policeman walk down the street,
see your mama and go, "Break it up!"

1551
01:26:43,506 --> 01:26:46,506
- Stop!
- [Laughing]

1552
01:26:46,579 --> 01:26:48,717
Stop it!

1553
01:26:48,786 --> 01:26:51,437
Rest her soul.
[Laughs]

1554
01:26:51,506 --> 01:26:53,895
It's good to see you laugh again.

1555
01:26:56,242 --> 01:26:58,413
It's nice to have a reason to.

1556
01:27:00,371 --> 01:27:03,502
You know, I miss this Henry.

1557
01:27:03,570 --> 01:27:06,886
I wish he'd show up more often.

1558
01:27:20,242 --> 01:27:22,762
There.
We did it.

1559
01:27:24,722 --> 01:27:28,465
I'm gonna go to the church for a minute.
You go on inside.

1560
01:27:28,530 --> 01:27:30,635
[Closes Door]

1561
01:27:35,602 --> 01:27:38,057
- There we go.
- Thank you.

1562
01:27:38,130 --> 01:27:41,742
- Don't slip.
- I won't. Don't be long.

1563
01:28:02,930 --> 01:28:05,264
[Men Singing A Cappella]
% Our Father%

1564
01:28:05,330 --> 01:28:08,745
% Which art in heaven%

1565
01:28:08,818 --> 01:28:13,128
% Hallowed be%

1566
01:28:13,202 --> 01:28:17,261
% Thy name%

1567
01:28:17,330 --> 01:28:19,850
- % Thy kingdom come%
- Evenin', Pastor.

1568
01:28:19,922 --> 01:28:24,330
% Thy will be done%

1569
01:28:24,402 --> 01:28:26,573
% On Earth%

1570
01:28:26,642 --> 01:28:29,097
% As it is in%

1571
01:28:29,170 --> 01:28:33,360
% Heaven%

1572
01:28:33,426 --> 01:28:35,947
% Give us this day%

1573
01:28:36,018 --> 01:28:40,753
% Our daily bread%

1574
01:28:40,818 --> 01:28:42,728
% And forgive us our debts%

1575
01:28:42,802 --> 01:28:44,657
% As we forgive our debtors%

1576
01:28:44,722 --> 01:28:46,794
% And us You must not lead%

1577
01:28:46,866 --> 01:28:49,714
% Into temptation%

1578
01:28:49,778 --> 01:28:53,836
% But deliver us
from all evil%

1579
01:28:53,906 --> 01:28:56,623
% For Thine is the kingdom%

1580
01:28:56,690 --> 01:29:01,196
% And the power
and the glory forever%

1581
01:29:01,266 --> 01:29:07,824
% Amen% %

1582
01:29:07,890 --> 01:29:10,225
- We could sell ads.
- I think it could work.

1583
01:29:10,290 --> 01:29:13,072
- Sounds okay to me.
- Mr. Hamilton?

1584
01:29:13,138 --> 01:29:15,920
- Is that gonna slow us down?
- Excuse me, Mr. Hamilton.

1585
01:29:15,986 --> 01:29:19,402
- Yes, Bernita?
- Reverend Biggs is here to see you.

1586
01:29:21,426 --> 01:29:23,499
- Henry!
- Joe.

1587
01:29:26,929 --> 01:29:30,442
Uh... Joe...
I need to speak with you.

1588
01:29:30,513 --> 01:29:31,887
[Laughs]
Can we...

1589
01:29:31,953 --> 01:29:34,767
Go ahead. I have no secrets from
my own people here. In fact, sit down...

1590
01:29:34,833 --> 01:29:37,516
I've reconsidered.
I don't want the job.

1591
01:29:37,552 --> 01:29:41,262
- Let's go, guys.
- I can't leave my own people, Joe.

1592
01:29:41,329 --> 01:29:44,111
And they can't afford
to travel clear up here.

1593
01:29:44,209 --> 01:29:48,649
- And as far as moving, Julia and l...
- Henry, a deal is a deal.

1594
01:29:48,720 --> 01:29:51,503
My decision is final.

1595
01:29:51,569 --> 01:29:53,424
I'm sorry.

1596
01:29:53,489 --> 01:29:57,580
You're sorry.
Sorry is not good enough, Henry!

1597
01:29:57,649 --> 01:30:01,261
You don't get it, Henry.
I don't care about St. Matt's.

1598
01:30:01,329 --> 01:30:03,980
St. Matt's is where we've been,
not where we're going!

1599
01:30:04,049 --> 01:30:06,983
Only if people like you abandon it, Joe.

1600
01:30:07,056 --> 01:30:09,478
[Sighs]

1601
01:30:12,208 --> 01:30:14,412
You know, it used to be
you couldn't just pick up...

1602
01:30:14,480 --> 01:30:18,058
and move away from your own people
as soon as you made a couple of bucks.

1603
01:30:18,128 --> 01:30:20,911
There was nowhere else for us to go.

1604
01:30:20,977 --> 01:30:23,824
But at least our kids
got to grow up with their heroes.

1605
01:30:23,888 --> 01:30:26,987
Henry, I'm trying to be nice to you
because you and I go back a ways...

1606
01:30:27,057 --> 01:30:29,740
and the old reverend
was always real good to me.

1607
01:30:29,809 --> 01:30:32,623
But this is gonna happen
whether you want it to or not.

1608
01:30:32,689 --> 01:30:35,656
With all due respect, Joe,
how do you think you can make me...

1609
01:30:35,729 --> 01:30:38,412
Not you. The church.
It's coming down.

1610
01:30:38,480 --> 01:30:40,651
What's coming down?

1611
01:30:40,721 --> 01:30:42,892
The church is...

1612
01:30:42,961 --> 01:30:47,019
Henry, do you know why I am
a trustee of a church I don't go to?

1613
01:30:47,089 --> 01:30:51,977
Because your deacons
all came begging to me,
telling me how broke the church was.

1614
01:30:52,049 --> 01:30:55,147
I bought the mortgage.
That's right!

1615
01:30:55,249 --> 01:30:59,984
I own it, and it's coming down.
That land's worth a lot more to me
with nothing on it.

1616
01:31:00,049 --> 01:31:03,148
- You're gonna tear down my church?
- That's right.

1617
01:31:03,248 --> 01:31:06,827
- A-And build a mall and tennis courts.
- Tennis courts?

1618
01:31:06,897 --> 01:31:10,988
Henry, we're gonna turn
that neighborhood around,
attract some real money to that place.

1619
01:31:11,057 --> 01:31:13,097
- Oh, I see. Yeah.
- You see what I'm saying?

1620
01:31:13,169 --> 01:31:17,097
You think without me there to lead them,
the people will just cave in.

1621
01:31:17,169 --> 01:31:20,202
- That's why you got me here!
- No, Henry, I want you to lead them.

1622
01:31:20,272 --> 01:31:24,745
- But into the future.
- Whose future, Joe?
They don't play much tennis.

1623
01:31:29,041 --> 01:31:32,653
Joe, come back to the church.
See exactly who you'll be hurting.

1624
01:31:32,721 --> 01:31:36,812
See their faces, their families, their...
their children, Joe.

1625
01:31:39,409 --> 01:31:42,725
People are a lot tougher
than you think, Henry.

1626
01:31:46,448 --> 01:31:50,223
[Sighs] Henry, look.
Come on, they'll survive.

1627
01:31:50,288 --> 01:31:54,566
And you still think you care
about the things we care about?

1628
01:31:58,897 --> 01:32:03,087
"Hark! I hear Joseph
and Mary in the manger."

1629
01:32:03,153 --> 01:32:05,128
- That's what I say.
- Only louder.

1630
01:32:05,200 --> 01:32:09,226
[Louder] "Hark! I hear Joseph
and Mary in the manger."

1631
01:32:09,296 --> 01:32:12,645
Then Michael and Jessica come on...

1632
01:32:12,720 --> 01:32:15,655
and sing a really slow song.

1633
01:32:15,729 --> 01:32:19,078
It's not that slow,
and it's very pretty.

1634
01:32:19,153 --> 01:32:22,535
Meanin' to ask you,
you two have a fight last night?

1635
01:32:22,609 --> 01:32:24,976
No, Ma, we delivered
Christmas baskets.

1636
01:32:25,040 --> 01:32:28,618
- The gym socks were a big hit.
- Huh! I knew they would be.

1637
01:32:28,688 --> 01:32:31,470
- [Julia] That you were right about.
- Hi there.

1638
01:32:31,537 --> 01:32:33,424
- [Julia] Henry.
- [Grandma] Hello.

1639
01:32:33,488 --> 01:32:38,704
Dad, Jason got sick, and I'm gonna be
a shepherd in the nativity play.

1640
01:32:38,769 --> 01:32:42,446
- I won't have to say "baaa."
- Ohh.

1641
01:32:42,513 --> 01:32:44,815
- [Laughing]
- That's great.

1642
01:32:44,881 --> 01:32:49,420
'Cause someone very special
is gonna be in the audience
listening to every word you say.

1643
01:32:49,489 --> 01:32:51,376
Huh?

1644
01:32:51,441 --> 01:32:55,816
- Your mother and I figured out
what you'd like for Christmas.
- Yeah.

1645
01:32:55,889 --> 01:32:59,336
- [Jeremiah] Did you wrap it up?
- Not quite.

1646
01:32:59,408 --> 01:33:02,704
[Gasps]
Hakim!

1647
01:33:02,769 --> 01:33:06,064
I missed you.

1648
01:33:06,128 --> 01:33:08,103
[Laughing]

1649
01:33:08,177 --> 01:33:10,894
Ohhh.
[Laughs]

1650
01:33:10,961 --> 01:33:13,382
Is he going to stay
forever and ever?

1651
01:33:13,456 --> 01:33:17,286
Well, just 'til the new year.
Then after that, we'll see.

1652
01:33:17,361 --> 01:33:20,776
- [Both Cheering]
- [Laughing]

1653
01:33:20,849 --> 01:33:24,264
I have a secret to tell you.
My ambulance has a siren now.

1654
01:33:24,337 --> 01:33:26,703
[Hakim]
Really?

1655
01:33:26,769 --> 01:33:29,583
- [Jeremiah Praying]
God bless Mommy and Daddy...
- [Toy Siren Wailing]

1656
01:33:29,649 --> 01:33:31,503
And Grandma...

1657
01:33:31,569 --> 01:33:33,707
- [Hakim] And my grandma.
- Amen.

1658
01:33:33,776 --> 01:33:36,908
- Okay, guys, you ready?
- We did our prayers.

1659
01:33:36,977 --> 01:33:39,792
'Cause we were already on our knees.

1660
01:33:39,857 --> 01:33:43,599
Okay. It's time to get into bed now.
Come on.

1661
01:33:45,328 --> 01:33:47,150
Boing!

1662
01:33:47,248 --> 01:33:49,550
All right.
Good night.

1663
01:33:49,617 --> 01:33:51,788
- Good night.
- Good night.

1664
01:33:51,856 --> 01:33:54,344
No talking late now.

1665
01:33:54,417 --> 01:33:57,712
Close the door, please.

1666
01:34:00,177 --> 01:34:02,795
Okay.

1667
01:34:04,336 --> 01:34:07,118
- Wait 'til you meet Dudley.
- Who's that?

1668
01:34:07,216 --> 01:34:10,031
- The man in the gray coat.
- Huh?

1669
01:34:10,096 --> 01:34:12,878
- You remember.
- Oh!

1670
01:34:18,001 --> 01:34:20,903
Christmas is supposed to be...

1671
01:34:20,977 --> 01:34:25,003
the most joyous day of the year.

1672
01:34:47,440 --> 01:34:49,928
- Henry?
- Hmm?

1673
01:34:50,000 --> 01:34:53,316
- Would you like some hot chocolate?
- No, thank you.

1674
01:34:53,392 --> 01:34:55,497
I've got to check the fuse box.

1675
01:34:55,568 --> 01:35:00,075
If we put any more lights on that tree,
we're gonna blow up the house.

1676
01:35:20,592 --> 01:35:23,440
[Door Closes]

1677
01:35:28,112 --> 01:35:32,040
[Henry's Voice] Christmas is supposed
to be the most joyous day of the year.

1678
01:35:32,112 --> 01:35:35,080
But for St. Matt's,
it's a day to surrender.

1679
01:35:35,153 --> 01:35:39,244
Not because I'm going to preach
at another church,
as some may believe...

1680
01:35:39,313 --> 01:35:43,688
but because the people who own
the building are going to tear it down.

1681
01:35:43,760 --> 01:35:47,372
- Now, it's no one's fault.
There is no one to blame.
- Henry.

1682
01:35:47,441 --> 01:35:51,085
It just seems as though despite
our best efforts, our dream...

1683
01:35:51,152 --> 01:35:55,211
- my dream for St. Matthew's...
will not come to pass.
- Ohhh.

1684
01:35:55,280 --> 01:35:59,055
But let's remember the good things
we've shared over the years.

1685
01:35:59,120 --> 01:36:01,935
The laughter, the exploding boiler...

1686
01:36:02,000 --> 01:36:05,066
the sounds of voices raised to heaven.

1687
01:36:05,136 --> 01:36:07,951
I'll miss it all.
I thank you for your efforts.

1688
01:36:08,016 --> 01:36:10,667
I thank you for your friendship.

1689
01:36:10,737 --> 01:36:14,414
God bless you.
I love you all.

1690
01:36:21,776 --> 01:36:25,093
% Silent night%

1691
01:36:25,168 --> 01:36:28,430
% Holy night%

1692
01:36:28,496 --> 01:36:31,944
% All is calm%

1693
01:36:32,016 --> 01:36:35,147
% All is bright%

1694
01:36:35,248 --> 01:36:38,597
% Round yon virgin%

1695
01:36:38,673 --> 01:36:42,055
% Mother and child%

1696
01:36:42,128 --> 01:36:44,910
% Holy infant%

1697
01:36:44,976 --> 01:36:49,068
- % So tender and mild%
- [Doorbell Rings]

1698
01:36:49,137 --> 01:36:55,214
% Sleep in heavenly peace%
[Continues]

1699
01:36:55,280 --> 01:36:58,761
- May I help you?
- Good evening.
I'm Rev. Biggs' assistant.

1700
01:36:58,833 --> 01:37:02,575
- Wait in the living room, please.
- Thank you.

1701
01:37:02,736 --> 01:37:06,664
- % % [Piano]
- Okay, Bernita, I'll take care of it.

1702
01:37:06,736 --> 01:37:10,860
I ain't buying!
For God's sake, it's Christmas Eve!

1703
01:37:10,928 --> 01:37:13,000
For the sake of God indeed.

1704
01:37:13,072 --> 01:37:16,782
Henry Biggs sent you here. I told him
he's through. To hell with him.

1705
01:37:16,848 --> 01:37:21,256
No, to heaven with him, Joe. That's
a plan not even you could mess up.

1706
01:37:21,328 --> 01:37:25,419
- Look, I don't know who you are, but...
- I'm an angel.

1707
01:37:25,488 --> 01:37:28,423
- No, not yours.
- % % [Piano Continues]

1708
01:37:28,497 --> 01:37:32,293
No, I'm afraid yours
is a long way off.

1709
01:37:32,368 --> 01:37:35,630
I'm a very busy man,
and you're wasting my time.

1710
01:37:35,696 --> 01:37:38,380
Now, I'm giving 'em another church.
St. Matt's is...

1711
01:37:38,449 --> 01:37:42,126
% % [Piano Continues]

1712
01:37:55,248 --> 01:37:57,419
What is this?

1713
01:37:57,488 --> 01:37:59,823
It's like your past, Joe.

1714
01:37:59,888 --> 01:38:02,670
You can walk away from it,
but it's still there.

1715
01:38:05,648 --> 01:38:08,430
[Joe's Voice On Radio] What do you see
when you look at a place like this?

1716
01:38:08,496 --> 01:38:10,863
I'll tell you what I see.
Sterling Acres.

1717
01:38:10,928 --> 01:38:13,067
The latest development miracle
from Hamilton Realty.

1718
01:38:13,136 --> 01:38:15,820
I see 200 luxury apartments.

1719
01:38:15,889 --> 01:38:19,150
Over here, a 24-hour health club
right on the grounds.

1720
01:38:19,248 --> 01:38:22,095
- State of the art designer interiors.
- This thing is broken.

1721
01:38:22,160 --> 01:38:25,160
- The kind of home that you deserve.
- It's not even plugged in.

1722
01:38:25,232 --> 01:38:28,975
- [Radio Continues]
- That's very smooth,
however you did all this.

1723
01:38:29,040 --> 01:38:31,658
[Radio Stops]

1724
01:38:31,728 --> 01:38:35,023
But you gotta do
better than that.

1725
01:38:35,089 --> 01:38:38,056
Yeah... you gotta do
a lot better than that...

1726
01:38:38,128 --> 01:38:40,583
to get to me.

1727
01:38:43,696 --> 01:38:48,104
Have to do a whole lot better than that
to get to me.

1728
01:38:48,177 --> 01:38:50,151
Whoever you are.

1729
01:38:50,256 --> 01:38:53,103
Don't worry about who I am, Joe.

1730
01:38:53,168 --> 01:38:55,307
You won't even remember me tomorrow.

1731
01:38:55,376 --> 01:38:57,481
But remember this:

1732
01:38:57,552 --> 01:39:01,262
Look at the real price
before you close the deal.

1733
01:39:01,328 --> 01:39:05,103
- What's that supposed to mean?
- You know what it means.

1734
01:39:05,168 --> 01:39:08,299
Listen to your heart.
Do what it tells you.

1735
01:39:08,368 --> 01:39:11,052
You'll find your way.

1736
01:39:13,456 --> 01:39:16,587
[Applause, Cheering]

1737
01:39:16,656 --> 01:39:19,144
[Applause Continues]

1738
01:39:20,752 --> 01:39:25,357
[Jeremiah] Hark!
I hear Joseph and Mary in the manger.

1739
01:39:28,368 --> 01:39:32,907
[Louder] Hark!
I hear Joseph and Mary in the manger.

1740
01:39:32,976 --> 01:39:35,976
[Laughter]

1741
01:39:36,048 --> 01:39:39,463
[Yelling] Hark!
I hear Joseph and Mary in the manger.

1742
01:39:39,536 --> 01:39:42,351
- Where's Joseph and Mary?
- [Laughter]

1743
01:39:43,920 --> 01:39:45,775
Ohhh.

1744
01:39:45,840 --> 01:39:48,655
[Applause Continues]

1745
01:39:54,673 --> 01:39:56,527
[Sighs]

1746
01:39:56,593 --> 01:39:59,854
[Bleating]
See the infant, meek and mild.

1747
01:39:59,920 --> 01:40:03,663
[Together]
He is God's anointed child.

1748
01:40:03,728 --> 01:40:06,248
So celebrate this Christmas morn.

1749
01:40:06,320 --> 01:40:10,543
[Together]
For on this day, His son is born!

1750
01:40:10,608 --> 01:40:12,779
% % [Intro]

1751
01:40:12,848 --> 01:40:15,303
Julia.

1752
01:40:19,120 --> 01:40:21,771
I wanted to see you
to say good-bye.

1753
01:40:21,840 --> 01:40:25,615
No, no. I'll call the council
and tell them that we still need you.

1754
01:40:25,680 --> 01:40:28,298
Well, this is over
the council's head.

1755
01:40:28,368 --> 01:40:32,940
Way over their head.
Besides, it's time.

1756
01:40:33,008 --> 01:40:34,896
How can it be time?

1757
01:40:34,960 --> 01:40:36,902
It just is.

1758
01:40:36,976 --> 01:40:39,561
It's funny, you know,
I spent the last 30 years...

1759
01:40:39,632 --> 01:40:42,567
thinking I'd be happy
if I could just get back to this place.

1760
01:40:42,640 --> 01:40:46,535
Here? The council must send you
to some dead neighborhoods.

1761
01:40:46,608 --> 01:40:49,478
[Chuckles]
Well, dead is relative.

1762
01:40:49,552 --> 01:40:52,007
But now I know where I belong.

1763
01:40:52,080 --> 01:40:54,087
Is this because of me?

1764
01:40:54,160 --> 01:40:57,608
No. Mmm.

1765
01:40:59,760 --> 01:41:01,865
Well, maybe just a little bit.

1766
01:41:01,936 --> 01:41:04,424
You remember when you
asked me what you do...

1767
01:41:04,496 --> 01:41:07,977
when the flame between
two people goes out?

1768
01:41:08,048 --> 01:41:10,153
Yes.

1769
01:41:12,112 --> 01:41:15,625
The answer is:
You don't let it.

1770
01:41:18,960 --> 01:41:22,342
Will we ever see you again?

1771
01:41:22,416 --> 01:41:25,099
I don't know.

1772
01:41:25,168 --> 01:41:27,110
Well, let's see.

1773
01:41:27,216 --> 01:41:29,867
No. Not again.
[Laughs]

1774
01:41:39,536 --> 01:41:41,358
[Sighs]

1775
01:41:42,896 --> 01:41:47,304
% Or maybe a fisherman%

1776
01:41:47,376 --> 01:41:51,020
% Out on the sea%

1777
01:41:51,088 --> 01:41:55,659
% % [Continues, Indistinct]

1778
01:41:55,728 --> 01:41:58,543
- How can I thank you?
- You already have.

1779
01:41:58,608 --> 01:42:01,772
- God bless you.
- Thank you.

1780
01:42:01,840 --> 01:42:04,262
% Who would imagine%

1781
01:42:04,336 --> 01:42:07,980
% A king%

1782
01:42:08,048 --> 01:42:11,823
% It was so clear%

1783
01:42:11,888 --> 01:42:15,979
- Mrs. Biggs, here!
- Jessica, you still have
more songs to sing.

1784
01:42:16,048 --> 01:42:18,251
I'm wet.

1785
01:42:18,319 --> 01:42:21,898
Who would use
Baby Wet Wet for Jesus?

1786
01:42:21,968 --> 01:42:24,750
Mrs... Biggs, our Virgin Mary bailed!

1787
01:42:24,816 --> 01:42:29,355
People are gonna know
that's not in the Bible. Do something!

1788
01:42:31,888 --> 01:42:33,710
You better get out there.

1789
01:42:36,016 --> 01:42:37,838
[Sighs]

1790
01:42:45,488 --> 01:42:48,270
% % [Singing Continues]

1791
01:42:48,336 --> 01:42:52,907
% That the world
would be different%

1792
01:42:52,976 --> 01:42:56,424
% 'Cause you were alive%

1793
01:42:56,496 --> 01:43:00,042
% That's when heaven stood still%

1794
01:43:00,112 --> 01:43:04,846
% To proclaim%

1795
01:43:04,912 --> 01:43:08,774
% One day an angel%

1796
01:43:08,847 --> 01:43:12,971
% Said quietly%

1797
01:43:13,039 --> 01:43:16,585
% That soon he would bring%

1798
01:43:16,656 --> 01:43:20,933
% Something special to me%

1799
01:43:21,008 --> 01:43:25,743
% And of all of
the wonderful gifts%

1800
01:43:25,808 --> 01:43:29,223
% He could bring%

1801
01:43:29,296 --> 01:43:33,769
% Who would imagine%

1802
01:43:33,840 --> 01:43:38,542
% Who could imagine%

1803
01:43:38,607 --> 01:43:43,342
% Who would imagine%

1804
01:43:43,407 --> 01:43:51,885
% A king% %

1805
01:43:51,952 --> 01:43:55,814
- [Applause]
- Thank you.

1806
01:43:55,887 --> 01:43:59,149
Hurry up.
Come on.

1807
01:43:59,248 --> 01:44:01,736
- Mommy, was I good?
- Oh! The best donkey.

1808
01:44:01,808 --> 01:44:03,782
I'll do it.

1809
01:44:05,680 --> 01:44:07,851
- [Laughs]
- Not bad, man.

1810
01:44:07,920 --> 01:44:10,505
Oh, yes!

1811
01:44:20,560 --> 01:44:23,145
"Christmas is supposed to be...

1812
01:44:23,248 --> 01:44:25,965
"the most joyous day of the year.

1813
01:44:26,032 --> 01:44:28,782
[Congregation]
Amen!

1814
01:44:28,848 --> 01:44:31,848
But for St. Matthew's, today is..."

1815
01:44:33,776 --> 01:44:36,646
[Congregation Murmuring]

1816
01:44:38,735 --> 01:44:41,550
"For St. Matt's...

1817
01:44:41,615 --> 01:44:44,812
today is supposed..."

1818
01:44:44,880 --> 01:44:48,492
[Murmuring Continues]

1819
01:44:57,839 --> 01:44:59,879
Beloved...

1820
01:44:59,952 --> 01:45:02,702
God never promised us
a perfect life.

1821
01:45:02,768 --> 01:45:04,840
Amen!

1822
01:45:04,911 --> 01:45:07,213
He's saving that
for the hereafter.

1823
01:45:07,279 --> 01:45:09,167
- Oh, no!
- Amen!

1824
01:45:09,232 --> 01:45:13,422
While we're here on...
on this Earth...

1825
01:45:13,488 --> 01:45:16,619
there's some things
we just got to work for.

1826
01:45:16,688 --> 01:45:19,535
- Am I right about this?
- [Congregation] Yeah!

1827
01:45:19,600 --> 01:45:21,771
- He's not following the script.
- He's doing fine.

1828
01:45:21,839 --> 01:45:24,109
- It could be a job.
- Uh-huh.

1829
01:45:24,207 --> 01:45:27,556
- It could be a church.
- Amen!

1830
01:45:27,632 --> 01:45:30,981
- It could be a community.
- Amen!

1831
01:45:31,056 --> 01:45:33,903
- Could be a marriage.
- Amen!

1832
01:45:33,967 --> 01:45:36,488
But the good news is...
is that He gave us...

1833
01:45:36,560 --> 01:45:40,335
two secret weapons
to help us to succeed.

1834
01:45:40,400 --> 01:45:43,149
- Hope...
- Hope!

1835
01:45:43,248 --> 01:45:45,452
- And love.
- And love!

1836
01:45:45,520 --> 01:45:47,495
- Hope.
- Hope.

1837
01:45:47,568 --> 01:45:51,528
- That's all a prayer is.
- [Congregation Agreeing]

1838
01:45:51,599 --> 01:45:54,861
- And love.
- Love!

1839
01:45:54,927 --> 01:45:57,742
- Loving is giving...
- Yeah!

1840
01:45:57,807 --> 01:45:59,847
- Pure and simple.
- Amen!

1841
01:45:59,920 --> 01:46:03,848
But in love,
there is also forgiveness.

1842
01:46:03,919 --> 01:46:06,603
- [Murmuring]
- And forgiveness...

1843
01:46:06,672 --> 01:46:08,614
belongs to everyone.

1844
01:46:08,688 --> 01:46:10,597
- It's a right.
- Yeah!

1845
01:46:10,672 --> 01:46:13,290
- Like a right to breathe or eat.
- Yeah!

1846
01:46:13,360 --> 01:46:16,295
Or even to fall in love.

1847
01:46:16,368 --> 01:46:19,117
Amen!

1848
01:46:22,767 --> 01:46:26,793
Sometimes we...
we take love for granted.

1849
01:46:28,240 --> 01:46:31,818
- Am I right about it?
- [Congregation Agreeing]

1850
01:46:31,888 --> 01:46:34,822
Those who are nearest to us...

1851
01:46:34,895 --> 01:46:37,132
dearest to us...

1852
01:46:39,087 --> 01:46:42,436
those are the ones
we forget to cherish.

1853
01:46:42,512 --> 01:46:45,000
But the miracle is...

1854
01:46:45,072 --> 01:46:47,974
when we love someone...

1855
01:46:48,048 --> 01:46:50,120
we are really loving God.

1856
01:46:50,192 --> 01:46:52,047
[Congregation Murmuring]

1857
01:46:52,112 --> 01:46:55,341
Look in wonder at those you love...

1858
01:46:55,407 --> 01:46:59,052
for they are the face of God.

1859
01:46:59,120 --> 01:47:01,421
- Hallelujah.
- Hallelujah.

1860
01:47:01,488 --> 01:47:03,877
And when the path is dark...

1861
